                <h2 data-uuid="db23a40ce30a48b3b2b21c6c447bfcb9"> Document-Based Investigation</h2>
            </div>
            <h3 data-uuid="07dac33c6edc4e16b94dbe0630f12e2f">Part 2: Write an Explanatory Essay</h3>
            <h6 data-uuid="563ba788907e4486a7a8fc9c98c259f9">Historical Context</h6>
            <p data-uuid="0a58fc4aaad1416dbf383b672d7fabef">The rise of totalitarianism and the desire of Germany and Japan for expansion of territory led to conflict overseas. At first, the United States tried to remain
                neutral, but the Japanese bombing of Pearl Harbor put an end to that plan. The war brought
                major changes to Americans. Many young men joined the fight in Europe and the
                Pacific while those who stayed behind made sacrifices of their own.</p>
            <h6 data-uuid="0be0753796304c23a0fc8614a43fc3d3">Task</h6>
            <p data-uuid="554a14f1ef504faa832fd14b37b7a5f4">Americans of all ages and backgrounds pitched in to help the
                United States and its allies win the war. Write an explanatory essay in which
                you tell how they helped and why they put so much effort into winning a war
                fought overseas.</p>
            <p data-uuid="8b06db5bf6594fcd9679cd060ba947a6">Complete the following steps as you plan and compose your essay.</p>
            <ol data-uuid="e37bf913a02c4800b204025ba91e2571">
                <li data-uuid="e0216f6f4b0442aba5c9235354072648">Review your notes and sources before you start writing.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="87d7c09ca4be4bed985520102c1db72b">Use at least <i>four</i> of the sources in Part 1, and develop the topic with relevant, well-chosen text or visual evidence from the documents.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="6de4a0fab07e4ecab315aab5986707a9">Cite specific text or visual evidence from each of the sources in your response.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="f4c33b47d8ae4b0694a312dfaa6880f2">Plan your essay so that it includes an introduction, several body paragraphs, and a concluding paragraph.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="021e8b99545c471498415dc30d5164e1">Establish a formal tone and use transitions to improve the flow of your writing, connect ideas, and clarify meaning.</li>
                <li data-uuid="a815125f61b24d07aad93e8fab905d5a">Organize your essay in a clear way that focuses on the topic and supports it with well-chosen facts, details, and examples.</li>
                <li data-uuid="7fe339cf7d094b1e9580153b0c52390c">Use precise, descriptive language and social studies terms to explain your topic.<br />
                </li>
                <li data-uuid="64cb35992b8c47efbf3d7aab1f176ab6">Write a conclusion that sums up your ideas and supports the information you present.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
